sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1307
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: M13 is a filamentous phage that infects E. coli. It packages a single stranded genome of ~6400 bases, encoding 11 ORFs. The M13K07 sequence entered here includes the entire M13 genome as well as a sequence from pACYC177 bearing the p15a bacterial origin of replication and a kanamycin resistance gene. These additional sequences were inserted into the packaging sequence of M13, enabling the phage to propogate as a Kan-selectable plasmid. The modification does attenuate phage production though plaques are still detectable on NEB strain ER2267 (genotype: : F?? proA+B+ lacIq Δ(lacZ)M15 zzf::mini-Tn10 (KanR)/ Δ(argF-lacZ)U169 glnV44 e14-(McrA-) rfbD1? recA1 relA1? endA1 spoT1? thi-1 Δ(mcrC-mrr)114::IS10). In the presence of a second plasmid bearing the M13 packaging sequence and origin, M13K07 serves as a "helper phage," providing the proteins for the phage coat but allowing the alternative plasmid to be preferentially placed in the phage capsid.
